# Flutter PDF Export Unicode Safety

## Mistake
Using `pdf` package default Helvetica and default `MultiPage` settings caused export failures for `₹` and large ledgers.

## Root Cause
- Built-in Helvetica in `dart_pdf` does not support Unicode currency/emoji glyphs.
- `pw.MultiPage` defaults to a low max page count, which throws `TooManyPagesException` for long reports.

## Required Recipe
- Always embed a Unicode-capable font (e.g. Noto Sans) from app assets and set it via `pw.ThemeData.withFont`.
- Load font bytes on the main isolate and pass bytes into `compute` args; do not read `rootBundle` inside isolate entrypoints.
- Set an explicit `maxPages` suitable for ledger exports.
- Sanitize free-form text (notes/category labels) to remove unsupported astral-plane glyphs when no emoji fallback font is bundled.

## Regression Test Pattern
- Add/keep a test that exports rows containing `₹` and high row counts, asserting no throw from PDF build path.
- Include at least one row with emoji-like input in note/category and verify export still completes.
